              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " MAKROFOL fission-track detectors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurement  of  the  reaction  cross section.",
                " After the etching  of  the  MAKROFOL  detector,  the",
                " identification and counting of fission fragments was",
                " realized by three observers for each detector, using",
                " optical microscopes. Finally-taking into account the",
                " factors of identification efficiency,  geometry  and",
                " track    counting,    as    well   as   effects   of",
                " self-absorption   by    target-photofossion    cross",
                " sections were obtained."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Statistical errors are presented."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Experimental results on fission cross section and the",
                " fissionability of the Au-197,  Pb-nat, and Bi-209 at",
                " photon  energies  60  and 64 MeV are presented.  The",
                " experimental photofission cross sections  were  used",
                " to  evaluate the total nuclear photoabsorption cross",
                " sections: sig(g,abs)=0.089*a**0.97 mb at en = 60 MeV",
                " and  sig(g,abs)  = 0.060*a**1.042 mb at en = 64 MeV.",
                " The photon beam was  obtained  by  backward  Compton",
                " scattering   of   laser   light   on  the  electrons",
                " circulating in ADONE storage ring. The main features",
                " of  this  beam  are a satisfactory energy resolution",
                " (up to 10%  fwhm,  at maximum energy),  an extremely",
                " low  background  (about  5%  integrated  over  whole",
                " spectrum above 2 MeV),  an intensity of about  10**5",
                " g/s and almost complete linear polarization."
              ]
            }
          ],
